625
01:06:57.440 --> 01:06:58.540
She works for Donald Trump.

626
01:06:59.140 --> 01:07:00.240
She works in Washington.

627
01:07:00.240 --> 01:07:01.500
Her name is Kellyanne Conway.

628
01:07:01.500 --> 01:07:02.580
Kellyanne Conway.

629
01:07:02.580 --> 01:07:05.980
I'm no fan of, well, I am a kind of a fan of Kellyanne Conway.

630
01:07:05.980 --> 01:07:10.580
She's quite a clever person, but she's awful in many, many ways.

631
01:07:10.580 --> 01:07:24.440
She's part of a, she's talking about various, so the interviewer says that Donald Trump is manipulating reality and all, you know, basically lying, which is true.

632
01:07:25.340 --> 01:07:27.880
And then he says, well, these are the facts.

633
01:07:27.880 --> 01:07:31.180
And Kellyanne Conway says, yes, and there are alternative facts.

634
01:07:31.180 --> 01:07:44.620
She's not saying we've made, I mean, in fact, the reason it's a famous saying is that her boss really does deal in alternative facts or deals in facts that aren't facts.

635
01:07:44.620 --> 01:07:46.540
But that's not what she was saying in the argument.

636
01:07:46.540 --> 01:07:48.680
She was saying, yes, you quote those facts.

637
01:07:48.680 --> 01:07:51.620
And there are a bunch of other facts and you don't quote those facts.

638
01:07:51.960 --> 01:07:58.880
So you, the media, are pumping out a line and we're trying to pump out another line.

639
01:07:58.880 --> 01:07:59.960
Okay?

640
01:08:01.460 --> 01:08:11.260
So, I mean, I don't feel particularly sorry for her because she's defending a person who is a serial fantasist and maybe one herself.

641
01:08:11.260 --> 01:08:18.740
But what the actual words she's using, alternative facts, are not a reference to, oh, we can make facts up.

642
01:08:19.359 --> 01:08:22.740
She's saying there are other facts that you're not quoting.

643
01:08:22.740 --> 01:08:25.979
Like, you're misrepresenting or your omission.

644
01:08:25.979 --> 01:08:26.880
Yeah, your omission.

645
01:08:26.880 --> 01:08:27.560
Exactly.

646
01:08:27.560 --> 01:08:28.600
That's what she's saying.

647
01:08:28.660 --> 01:08:31.899
That's what she's saying when she's saying that.

648
01:08:31.899 --> 01:08:37.260
So, we then make that a symbol of her saying something else.

649
01:08:37.600 --> 01:08:56.720
And so, if you're a politician and you're in a press conference, or not that they have press conferences very often, but you're doing a doorstop or you're pumping out some words, you spend your time trying to make them bland but positive, and everyone leaves you alone.

650
01:08:56.720 --> 01:09:13.700
So, and what I'm talking about would be a way to reduce those incentives, and allow people to hear people speak, and try and work out what they mean, and then try and work out what they think in response to those things.

651
01:09:15.840 --> 01:09:19.399
Okay, that explains definitely a lot of things.

652
01:09:19.399 --> 01:09:28.800
So, maybe we'll go back into your proposal of the private citizen juries as a way of showing the public that there is something.

653
01:09:28.800 --> 01:09:34.399
Exactly, and so what I would like to do, so I would like to do this as a form of activism.

654
01:09:34.399 --> 01:09:41.859
So it's not a pilot project or a demonstration project, it is a form of activism.

655
01:09:42.520 --> 01:09:50.200
And over time, as people saw this, they would say, hey, that's a good way for our democracy to work.

656
01:09:50.200 --> 01:10:06.440
About 90 odd percent of the people participating in these citizen juries, about 90 percent or 95 percent of them say this was really good, and about half of those think it's just life-changingly good.

657
01:10:06.760 --> 01:10:12.720
They have an epiphany that, yes, this is what a political system should be like.

658
01:10:12.720 --> 01:10:26.140
And in fact, Aristotle, the great ancient Greek philosopher, described democracy as a system in which people take turns in governing and being governed.

659
01:10:26.140 --> 01:10:28.300
And that isn't the system we have at the moment.

660
01:10:28.300 --> 01:10:32.900
The system we have at the moment is that people vote for people to govern.

661
01:10:34.440 --> 01:10:35.540
I like that quote.

662
01:10:35.540 --> 01:10:38.620
So yeah, thank you very much.

