01:11:20.800 --> 01:11:27.780
So I'm trying to make contact with Jeff Bezos, and I'm kind of shaking various trees because you can't just write a Jeff email.

675
01:11:28.300 --> 01:12:21.760
But I've been talking to people I know, quite senior people I know in politics in America, here, and in, that's Australia, and in the UK to try and find a way to represent to whoever's looking after that $10 billion and say, give us, I mean, for instance, one proposal is that in countries like Australia and the United Kingdom, sorry, Australia and the United States, who are tremendous laggards on climate change, that the money is used to hold a citizen jury on that subject, and that we send a delegation from the Citizens' Assembly or the Citizen's Jury to Glasgow for the Conference of the Parties 25 in November, which is on climate change, for instance.

676
01:12:21.760 --> 01:12:24.180
Have you heard about the Coalition of Everyone?

677
01:12:24.180 --> 01:12:27.720
I remember I was contacted by them not too long ago.

678
01:12:27.720 --> 01:12:39.340
And I think they might have started recently, but what they're trying to do is sort of like a citizen jury, a mock citizen jury to try to get people to talk about climate change.

679
01:12:39.340 --> 01:12:41.340
So maybe I'll try to get them in touch with you.

680
01:12:41.520 --> 01:12:42.720
Yeah, well, you do that.

681
01:12:42.720 --> 01:12:50.940
But most people who are working in this area are activists themselves, and they're trying to bring about a particular result.

682
01:12:50.940 --> 01:12:57.000
And that's fine, good on them, but that's not what I'm talking about, because I'm not talking about trying to...

683
01:12:57.000 --> 01:12:58.520
Specific issues, not specific...

684
01:12:58.520 --> 01:13:00.980
No, no, nothing to do with specific issues.

685
01:13:00.980 --> 01:13:05.520
Setting this body up is not setting it up to come to any conclusion.

686
01:13:05.520 --> 01:13:07.500
It comes to its own conclusion.

687
01:13:08.200 --> 01:13:22.040
So, for instance, I was quite active in trying to get some money to run citizen juries on Brexit before Boris Johnson won the Prime Ministership and has now proceeded as far as he has.

688
01:13:22.040 --> 01:13:22.700
I didn't...

689
01:13:22.700 --> 01:13:23.300
I wasn't...

690
01:13:23.300 --> 01:13:32.380
Now, in fact, I was strongly anti-Brexit, and the money I got would have been pretty strongly anti-Brexit, because why would you give money to it if it wasn't?

691
01:13:33.580 --> 01:13:36.800
If you're pro-Brexit, you do nothing and you get Brexit.

692
01:13:37.400 --> 01:13:43.240
But the point was not to produce a citizen jury that would decide Brexit was a bad idea.

693
01:13:43.240 --> 01:13:52.120
The point was to run a proper independent citizen jury and then say, we want to know what the considered opinion of the people is.

694
01:13:52.120 --> 01:14:03.620
And to go further, while I thought then and think now that Brexit is a minor disaster for the United Kingdom and for its politics, I might add.

695
01:14:03.620 --> 01:14:08.240
